@NODE MAIN "BRET-HAWNES"
     Name         : BRET-HAWNES

     Aliases      : No Aliases

     Type/Size    : File/2608

     Clone        : BEETHOVEN

     Symptoms     : After 20 Minutes a message.

     Discovered   : ?

     Way to infect: File infection

     Rating       : Harmeless

     Kickstarts   : 1.2/1.3/2.0

     Damage       : Tracks will be damaged.

     Manifestation: -

     Removal      : Delete File.

     Comments     : If you are starting the BRET-HAWNES virus it copies
                    itself always to the same memory-address $7F000.
                    After that it installs a new intrerrupt in the
                    Zero-Page ($6C). To stay resident it uses the KICK
                    Vectors & to infect other disks it finally patches
                    the OpenNewLib()-Vector.
                    If you are now booting with an unprotected disk the
                    virus creates the virusfile in the ROOT-Dir with
                    the name: $C0A0E0A0C0.
                    (If you make a dir you can see strange signs !!)
                    Then it modifies the Startup-Sequence with the
                    virusname.
                    After 20 Minutes the virus gives out a message which
                    says the following (over the new $6C interrupt!):

               GUESS WHO`S BACK ??? YEP. BRET HAWNES BLOPS YOUR SCREEN
                    I`VE TAKEN THE CONTROLL OVER YOUR AMIGA!!!
                 THERE`S ONLY ONE CURE: POWER OFF AND REBOOT ! ! ! ! 

                    After the 10th infection tracks will be damaged.

                    Click on this gadget to see a @{" Demo " SYSTEM V-IFF:BRET-HAWNES} of the Bret-Hawnes
                    virus. Push left mouse button to return.

A.D 04-94
@ENDNODE
